<sect1>
	<title>Accessing the Program</title>
<para>
Gpe-Rosetta is accessable in the settingsfolder. To access it tap on the Rosetta Trainer icon.
<figure>
	<title>GPE Main Screen</title>
<mediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref="settingsfolder.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject></mediaobject>
</figure>
<figure>
	<title>Main Application Screen</title>
<mediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref="mainappscreen.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject></mediaobject>
</figure>
</para>
</sect1>
<sect1>
	<title>Icon Explanations</title>
<para>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><mediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref="gotolast.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject></mediaobject><literallayout>Go to the begining of the database.</literallayout></listitem>
<listitem><mediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref="back.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject></mediaobject><literallayout>Go to the previous item in the database.</literallayout></listitem>
<listitem><mediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref="forward.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject></mediaobject><literallayout>Go to the next item in the database.</literallayout></listitem>
<listitem><mediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref="gotolast.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject></mediaobject><literallayout>Go to the Last Item in the database.</literallayout></listitem>
<listitem><mediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref="paintbrush.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject></mediaobject><literallayout>Learn a stroke.</literallayout></listitem>
<listitem><mediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref="quit.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject></mediaobject><literallayout>Exit The Application.</literallayout></listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</para>
</sect1>
<sect1>
	<title>Using the Application</title>
<para>
To train for you handwritting:
<orderedlist>
<listitem><para>Use the arrows in the program to find the selected character.</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Write in the blank box under the toolbar.</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Your stroke will then replace one of the two options of strokes for that character.</para></listitem>
</orderedlist>
Next to the training tab is the test tab. You can then test out your strokes and see if they are recognized.
<figure>
	<title>Testing Strokes</title>
<mediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref="teststrokes.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject></mediaobject>
</figure>
</para>
</sect1>
